# Screen Structure Rule

- All screens must follow this structure: `src/screens/<ScreenName>/<ScreenName>.tsx` with a sibling `styles.ts`.
- Keep screen UI logic in `<ScreenName>.tsx` and move StyleSheet definitions to `styles.ts`.
- Use existing shared components (for example `AppButton`) instead of duplicating UI primitives.
- All user-facing screen text must come from translation locale files (no hardcoded UI text in screen components).
- Use vector icons for screen UI icons (for example `react-native-vector-icons`); do not use plain text or emoji as icons.
